Package com.tiyb.tev.exception

Contains any exceptions defined across the application.

See: Description

  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    BlogMismatchParsingException
    Raised when Conversation XML is being parsed, and the name of the blog in the Metadata doesn't match the name of the blog in the XML.
    BlogPostMismatchException
    Raised by the API when a post is being updated, but the ID specified to the API and the ID in the post don't match.
    ExistingTagException
    Exception raised when a hashtag is created for no blog, but it already exists in the system for some blog
    InvalidConvoParentException
    Thrown for cases when a conversation is attempted to be updated but there is a mismatch in blog name
    InvalidTypeException
    Class representing attempted usage of a "type" that doesn't exist in Tumblr/TEV
    NoMetadataFoundException
    Raised in cases where there is no MD object in the DB
    NoParentPostException
    Exception raised when a sub-type is being inserted into the system (e.g.
    NoStagedPostsException
    Exception returned when a user attempts to download staged posts, but there are no staged posts to download.
    ResourceNotFoundException
    Exception thrown when a resource (any resource) is not found.
    UnableToDeleteMetadataException
    Exception raised when a metadata object is attempted to be deleted, but business logic prevents the action
    XMLParsingException
    Exception raised when an XML document can't be parsed successfully.

Package com.tiyb.tev.exception Description

Contains any exceptions defined across the application.
